item.description:
&lsquo;This is a machine that allows you to practice web app hacking and privilege escalation&rsquo;
TryHackMe -Basic Pentesting- is an easy room that only required knowing the basics. Primarily, the only tools you will need are:
Nmap gobuster Smbclient SSH Hydra John the Ripper Also, if you don&rsquo;t know how to enumerate and exploit smb, it would be a good idea to do Network Services Room before you start the Basic Pentesting Room.

Since bspwm doesn&rsquo;t handle any keyboard input we need to use a third party program such as, sxhkd or polybar to switch between keyboard layouts.
1. Create a script First we need to create a script that switch between languages. Here is an example for a bash script that switch between English and Arabic:
#!/bin/bash # Switching between keyboard layouts CURRENT_LAYOUT=$(setxkbmap -query | awk &#39;NR==3{print $2}&#39;) if [ &#34;$CURRENT_LAYOUT&#34; = &#34;us&#34; ]; then # To switch to arabic setxkbmap &#34;ar&#34; else setxkbmap &#34;us&#34; fi Then, make the script executable using chmod +x command.
